# My Java Genie - Workshop VM environment variables
#
# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in your OpenAI API key BEFORE starting the app:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   nano .env   (or: code .env)
#
# Get your API key at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Each participant should use their OWN key. The key is read at runtime only and
# is NOT included in the exported VM (OVA).

OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional overrides (the defaults in application-workshop.yml are fine for the workshop):
# COLLECTION_NAME=java25_docs_workshop
# VECTOR_DB_URL=http://chromadb:8000
